05. Square - 2 (For Loop)

Write a program that reads a number M and prints a Square of M rows and M Columns using numbers.

1111
2222
3333
4444

Note
• Use For loop.

Input
The input will be a single line containing an integer representing M.

Output
The output should be M rows and M columns containing Numbers as a Square shown in the sample output.

Explanation
For example, if the given number is M = 4
• Print the numbers on 4 rows and 4 columns as shown in the given image.
https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/square-2.png
The output should be,

1111
2222
3333
4444

Sample Input 1:

4

Sample Output 1:

1111
2222
3333
4444

Sample Input 2:

5

Sample Output 2:

11111
22222
33333
44444
55555

Solution

number = int(input())

number_of_rows = int(input())

for each_number in range(1, number_of_rows + 1):
    row = str(each_number)
    print(row * number_of_rows)

